race.description: Rsl Sa, Nt And Broken Hill Handicap (58)
race.comment: WARRANDYTE ROAD (6) added another strong win to the tally last start over a similar trip and looks to have really clicked into gear. The 3kg claimer sticks, he draws favourably, and he maps to get every chance again. Big hope to go back-to-back. AITCH D'AMICO (2) hasn't threatened in his last three, but he's been contesting tougher races. This is much more suitable, he loves this venue, and the rise in trip is a plus. With Price back aboard and a soft draw, sharp improvement is on the cards. ALLEGEDLY (3) continues to savage the line and is a genuine course specialist. Toeroek reunites after steering him to victory here on December 10. Sure to be very competitive. SHADOW HAWK (11) was solid first-up here over the mile and gets in light again. Draws to be prominent and has the platform to give this a real shake.
